Key Match Events: Andrew Wiggins scored 18 of his team-high 24 points in the third quarter of the Warriors' 121-113 victory over the Memphis Grizzlies.
Dennis Schröder tallied 17 points and nine assists, both personal highs as a Warrior.
Lindy Waters III began the second quarter by scoring eight straight points, including two 3-pointers and a layup off a backdoor cut.
Jonathan Kuminga exited the game with a right ankle sprain in the second quarter.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Warriors improved to 10-8 at home on the season and have won two of their last three games played at Chase Center and three of their last four games overall.
Golden State won the team’s sixth consecutive home game vs. Memphis.
The Warriors lead the season-series vs. the Grizzlies 2-1.
The Warriors improved to 11-2 when scoring 120-plus points this season.
Golden State improved to 10-4 when dishing out 30-plus assists and 4-0 when dishing out 30-or-more assists while making at least 50% of the team’s attempts from the field.
The Warriors improved to 5-0 on the season when shooting 50%-or-better from the field.
Andrew Wiggins scored a game-high 24 points, his 10th 20-point game of the season.
Draymond Green made three 3-pointers, the seventh time he’s recorded three-or-more 3-pointers in a game this season.
Trayce Jackson-Davis has now scored 10-or-more points in seven of his last eight games.
Buddy Hield made his seventh start of the season, recording 14 points, his 19th game scoring in double figures this season.
Dennis Schröder tallied 17 points, his highest scoring output as a Warrior.
Lindy Waters III made a season-high tying four threes en route to his seventh game of double-figure scoring on the season.
